&lt;p&gt;Staff Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A rare opportunity has arisen to joint the team on Ward 30&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward 30 is a 22 bedded unit which consists of 15 Haematology beds and 8 Supportive Care beds There is a Day Unit attached to the ward which all staff rotate through and a nurse led clinic area .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We provide care for patients undergoing treatment for blood cancers and haematology conditions and palliative patients with complex symptom management under the guidance of our Palliative Care Consultants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe our staff are our greatest asset and supporting our ward team to develop and grow creates a great place to work and enables us to provide safe compassionate care. We have a ward based Educator who will support and educate new starters&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ideal candidate will be caring, passionate and highly motivated to provide safe , innovative compassionate care in return we will develop you and support you within our speciality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSister Vicky WilliamsJob titleward managerEmail addressvickywilliams1@nhs.netTelephone number0151 604 7140Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sister Vicky Williams or Sr Zara Delamere&lt;/p&gt;
